attributeList.attribute: Required for the termination of protein synthesis which occurs when one of three stop codons (UAA, UAG or UGA) enters the ribosomal A site. eRF1 stimulates GTP binding to eRF3, inducing the GTPase activity of eRF3 that couples codon recognition and eRF1 peptidyl-tRNA hydrolysis to ensure rapid and efficient peptide release from the ribosome.
